params._members: Array of member addresses to add

params._hashOfDetails: Array of IPFS hashes for detailed info

returns._0: True if account can vote (has stake or reward-based voting power)

params._applicationId: ID of the skill verification application

returns._0: Total voting power (stake * duration + reward-based power)

params.disputeRaiser: Address of the party raising the dispute
params.oracleName: Name of oracle to handle the dispute

params._daoContract: Address of NativeDAO for stake verification
params._usdcToken: Address of USDC token for fee distribution

params._oracleName: Name of the oracle to check

returns._0: bool True if oracle is active
bool True if address is an oracle member

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC-1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

params._oracleNames: Array of oracle names to remove

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._status: True to grant admin, false to revoke

params._disputeId: ID of the dispute to settle

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

updateOracleActiveStatus(string).details: Only admins or OracleManager can call. Expensive operation - only call periodically.

params._oracleName: Name of the oracle to update

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

params._claimAddress: Address to receive fee rewards if voting wins
params._disputeId: ID of the item being voted on
params._voteFor: True to vote in favor, false to vote against
params._votingType: Type of vote (Dispute, SkillVerification, or AskAthena)
